== Curious Shit ==

What could he have possibly been charged with? His actions are legally sound. [[User:Aadieu|Aadieu]] ([[User talk:Aadieu|talk]]) 19:44, 9 September 2009 (UTC)

The attack on a civilian aircraft may have constituted a war crime. [[User:Opbeith|Opbeith]] ([[User talk:Opbeith|talk]]) 09:33, 1 March 2011 (UTC)
:Only a ''deliberate'' attack. I never saw any evidence he ''knew'' the aircraft he was shooting at was a civilian one. [[User:GregorB|GregorB]] ([[User talk:GregorB|talk]]) 10:10, 3 November 2011 (UTC)

That aside, what's with the article making a point of identifying seemingly every Croat in the Yugoslav National army, mentioning the other pilot who had nothing to do with the incident itself (but who was a Croat), and then failing to mention the nationality of the person who apparently ordered the attack -> Lt. Col. Opačić. Sorry, but this reeks of bias to me.
